cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SI

The paper discusses the properties of solutions obtained by training neural networks using gradient descent, which is a common technique in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also focuses on the regularization of neural networks, which is a topic in both cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions using neural networks for approximation tasks, which is relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
